    "faq": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How long before I see results?",
            "row_content": "<p>Most customers notice a visible difference within 2–3 weeks of consistent daily use. For best results, use RevitalEyes for 10 minutes each morning. Clinical studies show optimal results are achieved after 4–6 weeks of regular use. Many users report reduced puffiness within the first week!</p>"
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is it safe to use around the eyes?",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes! RevitalEyes is FDA cleared and specifically designed for the delicate under-eye area. The wavelengths used (660nm and 590nm) are completely safe for use near the eyes and have been used in clinical settings for decades. Always keep the device at least 1cm from your eyelids and do not look directly into the light during use.</p>"
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How often should I use RevitalEyes?",
            "row_content": "<p>We recommend using RevitalEyes once daily for 10 minutes. Consistency is key — make it part of your morning skincare routine for the best results. You can safely use it up to twice daily if desired, but most customers achieve excellent results with once-daily use.</p>"
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What is your return policy?",
            "row_content": "<p>We offer a 30-day money-back guarantee. If you're not completely satisfied with your results, simply return the device in its original packaging for a full refund — no questions asked. We're that confident in RevitalEyes. Over 94% of customers keep their device and see lasting results.</p>"
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I use it with my eye cream?",
            "row_content": "<p>Absolutely! We actually recommend applying your favorite eye cream immediately after your RevitalEyes session. Light therapy has been shown to increase the absorption of topical skincare products by up to 40%, making your eye cream even more effective. Think of RevitalEyes as supercharging your existing skincare routine.</p>"
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How do I charge RevitalEyes?",
            "row_content": "<p>RevitalEyes charges via USB-C (cable included). A full charge takes approximately 1.5 hours and provides up to 30 days of daily use (one 10-minute session per day). An LED indicator shows you the battery status — red means charging, green means fully charged. Perfect for travel too!</p>"
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "faq_7": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is RevitalEyes suitable for all skin types?",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes! RevitalEyes is designed for all skin types including sensitive skin. The 660nm red light and 590nm amber light wavelengths are gentle, non-thermal, and safe for all skin tones. If you have any specific medical conditions affecting your eyes or skin, please consult your healthcare provider before use.</p>"
          },
          "blocks": {}
        }
      },
      "block_order": ["faq_1","faq_2","faq_3","faq_4","faq_5","faq_6","faq_7"],
